{
  "stem": "23090.3",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But in actuality, that apartment where we lived, OK, was very close to her apartment where she lived.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So it was a matter of maybe a day or so, or two days.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We-- when we talk in those days, we don't talk weeks and months.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's hours and minutes and it's-- it's something that-- that you don't think long.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Everything is from day to day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we basically left at about the same time.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, we were not found.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were-- we heard the-- the-- the-- the noises of the-- of the search and conversation.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she was there, right there, and she was-- I'll tell you, she-- doctors in the ghetto were very privileged, because the Germans didn't have doctors.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And believe it or not, they would go to the Jewish doctors if they-- if-- because of their fronts and their-- and their-- they were, at that point, starting to feel the wrath of the-- of the-- of their fronts and the-- and both in Russia and somewhere, so, and the American side.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That all their doctors were being sent to all the fronts.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they would rely on the Jewish doctors.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "If they had something seriously wrong with them or whatever, they would firstly go to-- they would incor-- they would enlist a Jewish doctor to diagnose their-- their problem.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It sounds a little bizarre, but it is a fact.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I don't care who says that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's the way it was.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it's not by choice that they did it, but it was just another way of surviving for them.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So as a doctor, she was a little bit more-- in terms of when they would go and search the house, they too had their own little interest in-- in mind.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
